926e5448e8#-#926e5448e803b5d85e41f555bf22040f43fbf4c1#-#Ext Luka Juh#-#ext_luka_juh@hpe.com#-#20100108#-#1262944759#-#CRID=21388 Added a new API (srdex_add_recovery_host()) to the srdx library. This API adds an arbitrary host (a host that is not specified inside the cell_info file) to the host list. If the host already exists in the list, it is not added, only its list index is returned (the function succeeds). Internally, the function behaves similarly as omnirsh utility when called with INFO option; it contacts OmniInet on the remote machine in order to determine its operating system and Data Protector status. Once this information is obtained, the host is added to the host list and its current index (as well as the total number of hosts) is returned to the caller. POF-MERGE(CRID21388FROM/svn/bio-im-dp-sources/trunk) to revision 9444
